','2012-02-15 07:31:37','An encounter is a euphemism used in South Asia especially in India to describe extrajudicial killings in which police or armed forces shoot down suspected on this blog...',0,'1','','',0,0),(51,564,'Wilman','wngeybhigu@gmail.com','','114.124.29.73','2015-06-03 08:44:45','2015-06-03 08:44:45','Great!!! Finally i can solve my problem. Many thanks.',0,'1','','',0,0),(52,564,'siebzehn','geigenkasten@t-online.de','','93.214.47.129','2017-10-07 07:42:03','2017-10-07 07:42:03','Hey, thank you very much. I was quite puzzled after encountering the problem mentioned above. Who would have thought that there would be such an easy solution? Now I can do what I wanted to do, thanks a lot!',0,'1','','',0,0),(53,566,'Claire','claire_sells@yahoo.co.uk','','80.189.194.181','2012-05-29 09:55:02','2012-05-29 09:55:02','Hi Chris, thanks for this article.\nIt is a pain to try and print from the iPad to a printer.\nI wanted to print an artwork PDF from my iPad and all I have is a 2010/11 HP LaserJet which of course isn\'t AirPrint enabled. Somebody mentioned that there are various third party apps that you can install and that they found Print by EuroSmartz a good option :) It works for me!',0,'1','','',0,0),(54,566,'Chris','chris@birchwood-church.org','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','212.140.246.20','2012-05-29 13:28:06','2012-05-29 13:28:06','Cheers Claire, glad you\'re sorted. I tried EuroSmartz WePrint too; it has more features but I felt Activator \'just worked\' quite simply so I stuck with it.',0,'1','','',53,2),(55,596,'Tabatha','tabathamickey@gmail.com','http://amoralanaturaleza.com/AReasoner','198.23.151.122','2014-03-30 18:36:09','2014-03-30 18:36:09','Good day! This post couldn\'t be written any better! Reading through this \npost reminds me of my previous room mate! He always kept talking about this.\nI will forward this post to him. Fairly certain he will have a good read.\nThanks for sharing!',0,'1','','',0,0),(56,640,'Ayo','e862425@rtrtr.com','','196.200.74.227','2012-06-28 07:43:41','2012-06-28 07:43:41','The file names must have been changed. Neither the distribution nor package files for MacbookPro 7,1 are available on the server. Is there any other step available to determine the current file names?',0,'1','','',0,0),(57,640,'Chris','chris@birchwood-church.org','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','2.97.82.1','2012-07-07 22:32:28','2012-07-07 22:32:28','Hi Ayo, I still see MacBookPro7,1 in <a href=\"http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/33/54/041-2011/pRtCDYcWShMLxFggy3TzFzmfnnWQNFQBfJ/041-2011.English.dist\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/33/54/041-2011/pRtCDYcWShMLxFggy3TzFzmfnnWQNFQBfJ/041-2011.English.dist</a>, so I think 041-2011 is still the one you want?\nCheers,\nChris',0,'1','','',56,2),(58,640,'Dave','david_dh999@hotmail.com','','175.137.0.97','2012-07-31 12:58:52','2012-07-31 12:58:52','Hi i have a problem locating my mac model, macbookpro 9 1, would appreciate some help.\n\nThanks',0,'1','','',0,0),(59,640,'Chris','chris@birchwood-church.org','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','2.98.101.249','2012-08-01 17:03:51','2012-08-01 17:03:51','Hi Dave,\n\nI think the Boot Camp drivers for the new 2012 MacBook Pros are here:\n<a href=\"http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/11/05/041-0925/g27es04pw9re5ggrfp3vuf8ew6r53asfz8/BootCampESD.pkg\" rel=\"nofollow\">\nhttp://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/11/05/041-0925/g27es04pw9re5ggrfp3vuf8ew6r53asfz8/BootCampESD.pkg</a>\n\nWhich I got by finding your model number, MacBookPro9,1, in the .dist file just below it: http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/11/05/041-0925/g27es04pw9re5ggrfp3vuf8ew6r53asfz8/041-0925.English.dist\n\nIt looks like a 1GB download. Don\'t ask me how you get that on a CD, but let us know how it goes.\n\nChris',0,'1','','',58,2),(60,640,'nicholas','n.muraglia@gmail.com','','216.40.133.102','2012-08-02 07:30:25','2012-08-02 07:30:25','thank you so much for this!! I spent hours and hours trying to download the drivers through Bootcamp assistant, with no success. I was going crazy! \n\nThanks to you the download took less than an hour, and I have windows up and running now. woohoo!',0,'1','','',0,0),(61,640,'Chris','chris@birchwood-church.org','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','2.98.104.155','2012-08-02 13:04:46','2012-08-02 13:04:46','Hurray!',0,'1','','',60,2),(62,640,'Preston','prestonholden@live.com','','71.92.116.240','2012-08-02 22:35:02','2012-08-02 22:35:02','Hi, I\'m kind of stuck on bootcamp right now, so I\'m downloading this file on my PC, but I can\'t open the .pkg file to explore it\'s contents. Is there an alternative program to open it with?',0,'1','','',0,0),(63,640,'Chris','chris@birchwood-church.org','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','2.97.87.110','2012-08-03 09:51:33','2012-08-03 09:51:33','Hi Preston, I believe 7-zip will open .pkg files and will also open the .dmg file that you\'ll find inside the package file. Otherwise this page http://wiki.awkwardtv.org/wiki/Extracting_.dmg_files_on_Windows looks helpful.',0,'1','','',62,2),(64,640,'Steve','emp.dagaron@gmail.com','','31.9.74.154','2012-08-06 11:20:52','2012-08-06 11:20:52','hey chris, I\'ve download them but it didn\'t work, I\'m running windows 7 on my mac book air at the moment and I\'m stuck with it, can you tell me what to do please ?\nI don\'t know where to download boot camp assisstant ?',0,'1','','',0,0),(65,640,'Chris','chris@birchwood-church.org','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','78.145.93.102','2012-08-06 11:37:35','2012-08-06 11:37:35','Hi Steve,\nBootCamp Assistant runs under OS X and is preinstalled on your MacBook Air probably in /Applications/Utilities. But if you are already running Windows 7, you are past the point of needing BootCamp assistant, its purpose is to help you to get Windows installed, which you already have.\nSo all you now need is your hardware drivers. If you have downloaded the pkg file in Windows, you can open it with 7-zip. Then click down the folders to get to the contents. If it\'s a dmg file then open that with 7-zip too. There you will either find the drivers installer or you\'ll find an ISO file - a CD disk image - which you should be able to double click to open in Windows. And there the drivers installer.',0,'1','','',64,2),(66,640,'Kenny','kennyvimala@gmail.com','http://blah','110.137.209.142','2012-08-06 14:35:37','2012-08-06 14:35:37','Hey Chris,\nThanks a lot for this! I\'m running a mid 2012 macbook pro (MacBookPro 9,1) and used the http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/11/05/041-0925/g27es04pw9re5ggrfp3vuf8ew6r53asfz8/041-0925.English.dist file. Just telling that the file works here.\n\nAgain, thanks a lot!',0,'1','','',0,0),(67,640,'Javier','meetjavierwarhol@gmail.com','','114.79.49.46','2012-08-07 09:33:47','2012-08-07 09:33:47','Hi Chris,\nI have a Macmini 5,2 and have no idea which one I need to download. Yeah I\'m that bad in English :)\n\nThanks,',0,'1','','',0,0),(68,640,'Davran','forumtrack@me.com','','213.230.96.72','2012-08-07 12:16:03','2012-08-07 12:16:03','Hi Chris! Thanks for the great help with direct bootcamp drivers downloads!\nMy notebook\'s model number is MacBookAir4,2. Then, am I right downloading link with 2303 ending?',0,'1','','',0,0),(69,640,'Chris','chris@birchwood-church.org','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','78.145.93.102','2012-08-08 16:58:57','2012-08-08 16:58:57','Yes indeed, that\'s right.',0,'1','','',68,2),(70,640,'Chris','chris@birchwood-church.org','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','78.145.93.102','2012-08-08 17:02:31','2012-08-08 17:02:31','Hi Javier,\nThe \"041-2303\" download is the one that lists Macmini5,2, so you want to download http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/32/33/041-2303/W5jKtsQhhMgMXs3TKhPDqLXrpXyY2HdXMN/BootCampESD.pkg\nCheers, Chris',0,'1','','',67,2),(71,640,'ayman','ayman.k89@gmail.com','','85.112.95.23','2012-08-12 15:40:12','2012-08-12 15:40:12','I cannot thank you enough for this....I live in lebanon where there internet is .....well basically to d