ppreciated your kind help, thank you.',0,'1','','',320,0),(323,682,'Alex','rokenom@gmail.com','','217.115.65.17','2012-12-20 09:01:26','2012-12-20 09:01:26','The MacBookPro 9,2 doesnt work on my MacBook Pro, June 2012. Checked my hardware info, but Bootcamp tells me that these are not the correct drivers for the hardware i have.',0,'1','','',0,0),(324,682,'How to install Boot Camp on a 3TB Fusion Drive Mac | chrisl@dice.neko-san.net','','http://dice.neko-san.net/2012/12/how-to-install-boot-camp-on-a-3tb-fusion-drive-mac/','188.246.204.62','2012-12-20 16:50:00','2012-12-20 16:50:00','[...] Get Apple&#8217;s boot camp drivers (http://www.cafe-encounter.net/p682/download-bootcamp-drivers), extract and copy to the Windows USB [...]',0,'1','','pingback',0,0),(325,682,'Jim','jgbarre@yahoo.com','','24.22.252.242','2012-12-20 21:41:49','2012-12-20 21:41:49','Chris,\nThanks much for the file! As I was doing the install it was taking forever to download the drivers...so I did a search online and found your sight. Downloaded the file for my new MacBook Pro and it did the job!\nThanks again!',0,'1','','',0,0),(326,682,'Jim','jgbarre@yahoo.com','','24.22.252.242','2012-12-20 21:43:35','2012-12-20 21:43:35','I just dl the file for my new MacBook Pro 9,2 and it worked fine...',0,'1','','',323,0),(327,682,'jalvan','jalvan@msn.com','','223.207.66.147','2012-12-20 22:14:26','2012-12-20 22:14:26','well this bootcamp not working with windows 8 pro \nthere a lot of drives are missing , if anyone can help me ?',0,'1','','',0,0),(328,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','112.199.236.69','2012-12-22 03:34:26','2012-12-22 03:34:26','Hi Jalvan, sorry you\'re struggling, The first thing to get help is, to find out what model of mac you have. Follow the instructions above to find out your ModelIdentifier. If the instructions seem hard, ask a friend to help you?',0,'1','','',327,2),(329,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','112.199.236.69','2012-12-22 03:37:02','2012-12-22 03:37:02','Hi Vincent, thanks for posting the links, sorry for delay in your comment appearing. Can I ask what your ModelIdentifier is - does the BootCamp pkg not work? thanks for helping, Chris',0,'1','','',321,2),(330,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','112.199.236.69','2012-12-22 03:39:26','2012-12-22 03:39:26','Hi Alex, you\'re sure that your ModelIdentifier is 9,2? The main problem people have had I think, is incomplete download due to poor internet connection - the files appear to be there but the contents are incomplete - for which a download manager is the best solution',0,'1','','',323,2),(331,682,'nick','nhgould@gmail.com','','184.152.49.209','2012-12-24 02:50:16','2012-12-24 02:50:16','Hi - and thank you for the help!\n\nWhen you say \"install to a folder on your hard drive\" I\'m not sure what you mean... the installation of the package proceeds without giving me that option. It completes successfully, but I can\'t find the package contents.',0,'1','','',0,0),(332,682,'nick','nhgould@gmail.com','','184.152.49.209','2012-12-24 02:51:58','2012-12-24 02:51:58','Duh. Nevermind... I was missing the choose folder option in the install process. Sorry, it\'s late. :-)',0,'1','','',0,0),(333,682,'Simon','atone@126.com','http://www.yunaitong.cn','59.66.210.110','2012-12-26 06:25:50','2012-12-26 06:25:50','Hi, thank you very much for your article!\nI have Macbook Pro Retina 13 (10.2) and I tried many times to download bootcamp drivers directly from the Assistant but failed. Your article is just what I needed and it helps me a lot!\nGreat thanks.',0,'1','','',0,0),(334,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','119.73.249.114','2012-12-26 10:48:36','2012-12-26 10:48:36','Cheers Simon! ;-)',0,'1','','',0,2),(335,682,'Joseph','softworn@gmail.com','','68.59.53.85','2012-12-26 20:08:55','2012-12-26 20:08:55','This is pathetic on Apple and Intel\'s part. Just list the damn chipset and support it on all 3 generations for the platform. Stop trying to cover up the fact that these processors can support all of the Lucid Logix MVP features on the 6-series chipset. You\'re not fooling anyone. It\'s embarrassing enough to see what Intel is pulling with the lack of soldering on Ivy Bridge CPU\'s, but now they have decided to just toss all software support out the window? I will be ecstatic when the Linux kernel and alternative hardware vendors like ARM continue to prosper and knock these douche bags right off of their pedestals.',0,'1','','',0,0),(336,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','119.73.249.114','2012-12-27 01:33:33','2012-12-27 01:33:33','To my mind, if Apple just include a mini download manager in the BootCamp assistant this page wouldn\'t exist -- all I\'ve down is make Apple\'s software update download links available.',0,'1','','',335,2),(337,682,'Achille','achillechabran@gmail.com','','90.8.178.126','2012-12-27 12:31:08','2012-12-27 12:31:08','hi,\ni have the late 2012 mac book pro 13\'. my software is osx 10.8.2. which download should i get? its the non retina display.\nthankyou',0,'1','','',0,0),(338,682,'paul','paulbeard@mac.com','','67.161.86.33','2012-12-27 18:35:13','2012-12-27 18:35:13','Would it have killed them to put in a spinner instead of a progress bar? I had no idea the download was that large, I figured it was getting stuck.',0,'1','','',0,0),(339,682,'Faran','faran08@live.com','','182.186.186.183','2012-12-29 08:28:34','2012-12-29 08:28:34','Hi, I have macbook air 5,2.\nI downloaded the provided bootcamp drivers and installed on my laptop, in a random thought I tried to update my display drivers for better game performance, I downloaded latest intel hd 4000 graphics driver 15.1 from intel\'s site, but after installing it when I restarted my pc the driver actually crashes.\nOn intel\'s website it shows that my current display driver is 9.0 and latest one is 15.1, I want to get the latest drivers, what are the possible options?',0,'1','','',0,0),(340,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','112.199.179.248','2012-12-29 13:05:06','2012-12-29 13:05:06','First step would be to rollback, which hopefully you can do in Windows via a <a href=\"http://google.com/search?q=system+restore+point\" rel=\"nofollow\">system restore point</a>.\nSecond, you could boot back into OS X to double check the exact video hardware you\'ve got. After that, if it doesn\'t work you can\'t do much except wait for Apple to update drivers and publish a new BootCamp driver download.',0,'1','','',339,2),(341,682,'alanna','alanna.wells@ishb.co.za','','41.132.181.63','2012-12-31 07:17:41','2012-12-31 07:17:41','my mac is a macbookpro 8,1\nbut there seems to be no link for that...can anyone help?',0,'1','','',0,0),(342,682,'Randy','thephoenixfireandstone@gmail.com','','173.190.154.11','2012-12-31 09:19:55','2012-12-31 09:19:55','I have downloaded and ran the installer and now I can find the nested folders! Help plz...',0,'1','','',0,0),(343,682,'Randy','thephoenixfireandstone@gmail.com','','173.190.154.11','2012-12-31 15:04:05','2012-12-31 15:04:05','For those having a problem finding the disk image if you don\'t get the folder option at the installer the file path is: ./Library/ApplicationSupport/BootCamp/WindowsSupport.dmg\n\nCheers',0,'1','','',0,0),(344,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','180.129.98.74','2012-12-31 15:58:01','2012-12-31 15:58:01','Hi Alanna, search the table above again but with no space in macbookpro8,1 and you\'ll find it. Cheers, Chris',0,'1','','',341,2),(345,682,'Colin','jocosap@gmail.com','','71.197.15.185','2013-01-01 17:31:35','2013-01-01 17:31:35','Just wanted to say Thanks!!!\nYou are a lifesaver!!!',0,'1','','',0,0),(346,682,'Chr