ttom download link.\n-Bob',0,'1','','',341,0),(353,682,'Himanshu','himanshub43@gmail.com','','120.56.158.55','2013-01-06 03:11:28','2013-01-06 03:11:28','Hi Chris,\nI have an imac 2011,2 but recently upgraded it to mountain lion 10.8.2,so the bootcamp is now a version 5....  Should I download drivers for imac12,2 or for imac13????\n\nThanks in advance :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(354,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','87.114.10.251','2013-01-06 06:47:44','2013-01-06 06:47:44','It\'s the _Hardware_ not the software that matters -- if your modelIdentifier is 11,2 then download that.',0,'1','','',353,2),(355,682,'Himanshu','himanshub43@gmail.com','','120.59.25.238','2013-01-06 07:09:28','2013-01-06 07:09:28','I just did that...and it worked\n...Thanks a ton\n-Himanshu',0,'1','','',354,0),(356,682,'Wim','wim@wijninga-kamphuis.nl','','195.240.47.45','2013-01-06 12:55:38','2013-01-06 12:55:38','Hi Chris,\n\nNice Work! After a fatal upgrade from W7 to W8 on the Macbook Pro of my wife, I decided to go back to W7. W8 on the Macbook was a disaster! But the orginal Bootcamp CD was nowhere to find (was there one delivered ?, I don\'t know). Thanks to your instructions I got everything back to normal. Thanks!',0,'1','','',0,0),(357,682,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','82.132.225.233','2013-01-06 15:19:20','2013-01-06 15:19:20','Cheers Wim. May I ask what machine do you have  Win8 works fine for me on my MacBookPro5,2.',0,'1','','',356,2),(358,682,'Max','maxim.rotermund@yahoo.de','','93.207.125.100','2013-01-06 15:59:22','2013-01-06 15:59:22','I recently bought the macbook pro 9,2 and the disk did not come with it so i have to get the drivers onto a USB, but i can not find any link like you described above, What can i do ??',0,'1','','',0,0),(359,682,'Weyler Tomaszewski','weyler.tomaszewski@gmail.com','','189.121.237.164','2013-01-06 19:54:48','2013-01-06 19:54:48','Thank you 