of file is the Payload file? The file does not have any extension and is not by default associated with any application in Windows 7. What application do I use to open the Payload file? Without knowing the answers to these questions it is impossible to complete step 2 and move to step 3.',0,'1','','',0,0),(625,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-01-11 07:53:33','2013-01-11 07:53:33','Hi Kevin, if you did step 1 with 7-zip then at steps 2 and 3 you are still in 7-zip and within the 7-zip gui you click on the Payload file. 7-zip then opens it within the same window. Sorry it wasn\'t clear, Chris',0,'1','','',624,2),(626,860,'rodrigo','rodrigows47@gmail.com','','201.10.137.110','2013-01-21 07:14:11','2013-01-21 07:14:11','VALEU CARA MUITO OBRIGADO FUNCIONA MESMO\n\nPODEM BAIXAR E SEGUIR OS PASSOS\n\nVALEU BOA SORTE PRA VOC.',0,'1','','',0,0),(627,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-01-21 08:23:29','2013-01-21 08:23:29','You\'re welcome!',0,'1','','',626,2),(628,860,'izar ramlan','izar.ramlan@yahoo.com','','206.53.152.166','2013-01-22 02:32:38','2013-01-22 02:32:38','its realy clear, thx chris :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(629,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-01-22 05:12:40','2013-01-22 05:12:40','thank you!',0,'1','','',628,2),(630,860,'Rakel','ra@hotmail.com','','194.144.27.30','2013-01-28 23:32:28','2013-01-28 23:32:28','Thank you, this worked for me',0,'1','','',0,0),(631,860,'Joe','jrheit@sbcglobal.net','','68.73.58.176','2013-01-30 18:21:08','2013-01-30 18:21:08','Im stuck in windows first of all. then after i copy the o-apple_ISO to my desktop and rename it to .iso it turns into a disc image and i cant open it. windows keeps trying to burn it to a disc, why? help please',0,'1','','',0,0),(632,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-01-31 23:40:51','2013-01-31 23:40:51','Hi Joe, Turning into a disk image is correct, that\'s what it is. What should happen next is that Window mounts it as if it were a disk.\nIf that doesn\'t work try this instead: Instead of saving the 0.Apple_ISO to the desktop, just stay in 7-zip and double click it. Then, drag all the contents to an empty folder on the desktop.',0,'1','','',631,2),(633,860,'Bjrn Fridal','info@betafirm.com','http://betafirm.com','90.184.160.44','2013-02-01 21:06:40','2013-02-01 21:06:40','Thank you so much man. I got Windows 8 working on my Macbook now. Had a little trouble with not opening the .ISO file with Win7, but instead mouting it. The comments helped me out.\n\nCheers\nBjrn Fridal',0,'1','','',0,0),(634,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-02-02 23:04:35','2013-02-02 23:04:35','Cheers Bjrn. If you can suggest improvements to the notes / say which bit didn\'t work well I can update it, I\'ve tried changing the last steps a couple of times already but still not quite easy. Chris',0,'1','','',633,2),(635,860,'qayyum','qayyum.rosli29@gmail.com','','183.171.164.64','2013-02-03 11:55:11','2013-02-03 11:55:11','hey, im a newbie in mac, i installed windows in my macbook pro 9,2, downloaded the support software from your site, when extract the file is less then 6mb and nothing happened to it. eg: wifi and bluetooth, right click and audio. need help. thanks',0,'1','','',0,0),(636,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-02-03 19:07:09','2013-02-03 19:07:09','Hi qayyum, if you don\'t get the full size download then either retry it, OR I strongly recommend getting a download manager. I\'ve used <a href=\"http://www.igetter.net/\" title=\"iGetter\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.igetter.net/</a> a more recent one is <a href=\"https://eltima.cleverbridge.com/389/?affiliate=26456&scope=checkout&cart=80836\" title=\"Folx\" rel=\"nofollow\">Folx</a>',0,'1','','',635,2),(637,860,'Noah Jay','nijagameexpert@gmail.com','','93.31.122.208','2013-02-04 07:57:02','2013-02-04 07:57:02','Hey, I get most of this, just one question: once my files are extracted from the iso in windows (on my mac), how do I install them? Do I need to restart my computer with them on an intall drive, or something, or can I install them directly in windows?\n\nTrying to figure out whether to install windows now, and then download the files when I have a faster connection available, or to wait for that connection to have Boot Camp download them correctly...',0,'1','','',0,0),(638,860,'Admin','chris.5quid@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-02-04 11:05:03','2013-02-04 11:05:03','Hi Noah, in Windows, just double click the setup.exe. No restart or anything, just run the file.\nIf you install Windows before you\'ve got the bootcamp drivers, you will get a working mostly usable Windows install, it\'s just that the graphics won\'t be so fast and the nice Apple hardware features - camera, trackpad gestures - won\'t work.\nNB the easier way to download is on <a href=\"/p682/download-bootcamp-drivers\" rel=\"nofollow\">/p682/download-bootcamp-drivers</a>',0,'1','','',637,1),(639,860,'Peter jr.','perodaah@hotmail.co.uk','','78.157.202.166','2013-02-04 17:21:42','2013-02-04 17:21:42','Is there a way I can download on Windows and Copy it to my MacBook ? If Macs could read fat 32 drives this could be possible, but wondering if it would affect the PKG/DMG files',0,'1','','',0,0),(640,860,'Download BootCamp Drivers for Macs to run Windows 7 or 8','','http://soft-pedia.in/download-bootcamp-drivers-for-macs-to-run-windows-7-or-8/','209.190.85.76','2013-02-05 07:46:43','2013-02-05 07:46:43','[...] instead Computer itself Y, that&#8217;s increasingly difficult. You&#8217;ll need the exact help at  http://www.cafe-encounter.net/p860/opening-a-bootcamp-driver-download-on-windows-7-or-8-with-7-zip  to start a pkg data as well as the dmg computer database from [...]',0,'1','','pingback',0,0),(641,860,'Mike','it@millerhare.com','http://www.millerhare.com','217.138.12.100','2013-02-07 12:27:00','2013-02-07 12:27:00','This is fantastic. Thank you for such clear, detailed instructions.\nTrying to set up bootcamp without a network connection is impossible without this.',0,'1','','',0,0),(642,860,'Peter Vateha','peter.vateha@gmail.com','','91.127.111.1','2013-02-07 14:10:06','2013-02-07 14:10:06','Hi Chris, today I did instal with boot camp on my Mac, Windows 7. During the instalation I did click on \"download the latest version of windows support from apple\", but did not choose storage place on my usb driver :-(. then the instalation continue, finish and windows works, but can not get next step - instal the apple drivers  (setup - application). now, I do not know what to do. I tried to read your advises on this web page, but I am not very good in english, so I ve got trouble :-). Also I can get back to my mac, because during booting always windows starts, although I press and hold backspace button. There is no possibility to choose other boot driver. So can you help me also sending mi solution on my email: peter.vateha@gmail.com ? Thank you very much!',0,'1','','',0,0),(643,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','81.159.96.112','2013-02-08 09:24:31','2013-02-08 09:24:31','Hi Peter, If you don\'t specify where the download goes, I think it goes into /Library/ somewhere. The simple thing is just to start again from OS X and remember to choose a location.\n\nTo get back into Mac: as the computer starts up, hold down the alt key.',0,'1','','',642,2),(644,860,'James G','graham2017@ufl.edu','','174.64.98.105','2013-02-17 08:08:32','2013-02-17 08:08:32','Thanks for this post! I recently wiped my oct 2009 13\" macbook hdd clean and did a fresh install of windows 7. There are no traces of OSX on the laptop as of now. I downloaded these drivers and picked them out in 7zip and have them on my desktop. However, in the folder I see VISTAXP2K, si32.exe, si64.exe, ssetup.exe and a couple other files. When I click setup, not much happens except for a successful install of Motorola SM56 drivers. Still no functionality of trackpad or function keys. Any thoughts?',0,'1','','',0,0),(645,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-02-17 20:38:10','2013-02-17 20:38:10','Hi James, \nI\'m not sure. What\'s your model identifier & which link did you clock for your download? I can check if one of my links is wrong. \nAnd did the top level folder of your download look something like the picture at <a href=\"http://www.cafe-encounter.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/BootCamp-WindowsSupport.dmg-Contents.png\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.cafe-encounter.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/BootCamp-WindowsSupport.dmg-Contents.png complete with pdf?\nChris</a>',0,'1','','',644,2),(646,860,'Mikko H','mikko.heinonkoski@saunalahti.fi','','212.226.40.233','2013-02-19 09:58:21','2013-02-19 09:58:21','I had exactly the same situation than James G. I\'have early 2009 Mac Mini (3.1) with only Windows 7 installed, no OS X.\n\nTop level folder did not look like the picture you linked. Setup file was named ssetup.exe and for me too it installed (?) Motorola SM56 drivers. Any help is appreciated.',0,'1','','',645,0),(647,860,'Honey','mylaimadhu@gmail.com','','202.128.160.179','2013-02-20 02:10:27','2013-02-20 02:10:27','Thanks.. \n\njust wondered, why don\'t have the chance to download the exe files instead of dmg file?',0,'1','','',0,0),(648,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-02-20 13:24:52','2013-02-20 13:24:52','I don\'t really know - the dmg is what Apple offers for download.',0,'1','','',647,2),(649,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-02-20 13:44:01','2013-02-20 13:44:01','H Mikko, tell me which download link you used, and I\'ll see what I get (Mine\'s an older machine I haven\'t looked at the newer downloads)',0,'1','','',646,2),(650,860,'Hideaki Tadokoro','tadokorohideakik@gmail.com','','106.174.151.112','2013-02-21 20:39:47','2013-02-21 20:39:47','My Macbook is Unibody Macbook late 2009, macbook 6.1 .   I downloaded 632MB 23 May 2012 and I installed boot camp 4.0 (Windows drivers) from  WindowsSupport.dmg.   I don\'t think book camp 4.0 doesn\'t work in windows 8 pro.  \nCan this drivers work in windows 8 pro?    If this is true, I will install windows 8 pro into my boot camp (windows 7).   Please answer my question.',0,'1','','',0,0),(651,860,'daniel','daniel.krantz.x@gmail.com','','83.252.68.236','2013-02-21 20:43:06','2013-02-21 20:43:06','I downloaded http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/33/54/041-2011/pRtCDYcWShMLxFggy3TzFzmfnnWQNFQBfJ/BootCampESD.pkg for my imac (mid 2011, iMac12,1).\nAnd I experience the same problem as Mikko H describes: setup file was named \"ssetup.exe\" and only installed Motorola SM56 drivers.',0,'1','','',649,0),(652,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-02-22 08:37:01','2013-02-22 08:37:01','Hi, Windows 8 is working fine for me on a 2009 MacBook Pro, and for others. It is not yet officially supported by Apple. So there is no guarantee but you should be okay... Cheers, Chris',0,'1','','',650,2),(653,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-02-22 08:55:10','2013-02-22 08:55:10','Daniel, Mikko H, James G, I\'m pretty sure I\'ve experienced the same thing that you desceribe last year a couple of times. <em>But</em> when I downloaded the link that Daniel pasted in his reply using iGetter, and opened it up what I now see is the same as I posted in the pictures on  <a href=\"/p682/download-bootcamp-drivers\" rel=\"nofollow\">/p682/download-bootcamp-drivers</a> with the full set of drivers.\nGrasping at straws here but I wonder if it\'s possible that Apple has multiple servers for the url, and one of them\'s got the wrong thing on it? I don\'t know how else to account for it.\nTry doing the download 1 or 2 more times with a download manager and see what you get?',0,'1','','',0,2),(654,860,'erik','peterserikg@gmail.com','','192.138.214.123','2013-03-01 15:54:41','2013-03-01 15:54:41','All this does is install a motorola modem driver. Why?',0,'1','','',0,0),(655,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-03-01 16:15:31','2013-03-01 16:15:31','I don\'t know. I\'ve seen the same thing but when I re-downloaded the drivers again I got the full set as expected. Point 4 on this page <a href=\"http://www.cafe-encounter.net/p1118/direct-download-of-bootcamp-drivers-further-help\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.cafe-encounter.net/p1118/direct-download-of-bootcamp-drivers-further-help</a> is my current, possibly lame, best guess. If you retry the download from a different source ip and tell me what result you get I\'d be interested?\nChris',0,'1','','',654,2),(656,860,'Alpha','ojas.jetfire@gmail.com','','117.212.124.6','2013-03-01 19:44:13','2013-03-01 19:44:13','To all those with the motorola issue,\n\nextract o.Apple_ISO using 7-zip to the desktop (or somewhere)\nrename it to Apple.ISO\nmount it using PowerISO or simply extract the contents to a folder using 7zip.\n\nYou\'ll find that the rest of the drivers appear alongside the Moto ones. I guessed they were hidden or something because the size of 0.Apple_ISO was much larger than the sum of the moto drivers, turned out to be correct.\n\nCheers!',0,'1','','',0,0),(657,860,'erik','peterserikg@gmail.com','','98.217.66.226','2013-03-01 23:37:56','2013-03-01 23:37:56','Yeah Alpha, that worked perfectly. Thanks guys!',0,'1','','',0,0),(658,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-03-04 12:39:36','2013-03-04 12:39:36','Thanks Alpha, I change the instructions to match.',0,'1','','',656,2),(659,860,'Steve T','Steve@tindr.com','','99.241.77.203','2013-03-15 05:24:13','2013-03-15 05:24:13','My MacOS is completely corrupted... This saved me! Thank u so much!',0,'1','','',0,0),(660,860,'leo','leoatleon@gmail.com','','24.252.199.43','2013-04-11 20:38:22','2013-04-11 20:38:22','Hi there,\nI screwed up my Mac OSx. I dont have any CD either. I had to install windows 7 ultimate 32 bit and now i needed drivers for audio, blutooth etc. I found this. Everything makes sense goes to open the pkg but when I double click payload, it asks for using the related program to open this file. Which program i should use to open this payload? What extension is it? Or I am stuck at that point.\n\nOr Can you refer to a website where I could find the Apple.iso thingy. I am on Macbook pro',0,'1','','',0,0),(661,860,'leo','leoatleon@gmail.com','','24.252.199.43','2013-04-11 21:02:45','2013-04-11 21:02:45','Nevermind. I have got it but these files i already had. Its not ISO image. Or I have make an ISO image out of it and then setup drive in PowerISO and then install?......\n\nIts just stupid packaging. Typical apple  a*** holes!',0,'1','','',0,0),(662,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-04-11 22:52:32','2013-04-11 22:52:32','Hi Leo, If you downloaded 7-zip that one program should be all you need to open the pkg file and to open the ISO file you get inside it. Yes you could also use powerISO or something to mount it. Chris',0,'1','','',661,2),(663,860,'Rachit','rachitjpant@gmail.com','','74.70.215.90','2013-04-19 05:33:37','2013-04-19 05:33:37','Can u help me install windows 7 on my macbook2,1 os 10.4.11 . since it is an old macbook i am not able to install windows staightforward through bootcamp. Also my superdrive does not work. I have a windows bootable usb drive , which I am able to use to install windows on a pc.  i have so far installed refit on my mac and when i try to boot into my windows usb pen drive , I get a message : Not found from local deveice path ..the firmware refused to boot ... blah blah . Also I had copied the entire drivers folder using the method u stated above to the usb drive. I dont understand how these drivers would help me boot into my usb drive( as they are exe files - exe files run on windows as per my knowledge) .. .... Please help',0,'1','','',0,0),(664,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-04-19 11:14:16','2013-04-19 11:14:16','Hi Rachit,\nSorry, the drivers linked from my pages help you get all the apple hardware working properly AFTER you have got Windows up and running.\n\nGetting Windows installed without your superdrive working sounds difficult. Possibly harder than getting the superdrive fixed. Can you beg or borrow a USB  DVD drive and a Windows installer DVD?\n\nBest I can do is refer you to https://discussions.apple.com and to http://apple.stackexchange.com   if you post a question there you have a good chance of getting help.\n\nI take it you got as far as the instructions on this page: http://support.apple.com/kb/HT1948 ?\nTo start from a USB storage device that meets the above requirements, connect the device, then select it in Startup Disk preferences. Or, connect the device, restart, and immediately press and hold the Option key to access Startup Manager.\nIf you\'re using a MacBook or MacBook Pro, try using a different USB port if you cannot startup from the external USB storage device.\nIf you use Boot Camp, you may not be able to boot natively into supported versions of Microsoft Windows XP or Windows Vista operating systems installed on external USB hard drive.\n\nChris',0,'1','','',663,2),(665,860,'Emi','emilianofiorentino@hotmail.com','','186.19.74.47','2013-04-22 20:43:05','2013-04-22 20:43:05','Works great on macmini!\nThanks!!',0,'1','','',0,0),(666,860,'Dan','h2obubbli@hotmail.co.uk','','92.2.95.89','2013-04-29 22:47:57','2013-04-29 22:47:57','Hi \n\nMany thanks for this tutorial but after doing all of that when i run .setup it says \"bookcamp x64 is not supported......\"\n\nGuess my macbook model is just too old to handle windows 7? (2008-9 model) =/',0,'1','','',0,0),(667,860,'Chris F Carroll','chris.carroll@unforgettable.me.uk','http://www.cafe-encounter.net/','86.26.81.148','2013-04-30 10:38:07','2013-04-30 10:38:07','Hmm. So long as it has an x86 chip, you should be able to get it to work. \n\nFirst thing, check whether your Windows is 64 bit. If so ... do the Windows install all over again,  choosing 32bit Windows :-(\n\nThen, make sure you\'ve got the \"oldest\" set of drivers, which would be this one: <a href=\"http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/33/54/041-2011/pRtCDYcWShMLxFggy3TzFzmfnnWQNFQBfJ/BootCampESD.pkg\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://swcdn.apple.com/content/downloads/33/54/041-2011/pRtCDYcWShMLxFggy3TzFzmfnnWQNFQBfJ/BootCampESD.pkg</a>\nThat definitely includes 32 bit drivers.',0,'1','','',666,2),(668,860,'K.','benit84@yahoo.com','','165.98.223.21','2013-06-10 21:37:00','2013-06-10 21:37:00','after I run \"setup.exe\" in windows8 64 bit (no OSX), a window comes up saying it has installed correctly, and that is it. I restarted and attempted to update drivers in device manager which didn\'t work,  I am stuck on how to instal the drivers. please help.',0,'1','','',0,0),(669,860,'K.','benit84@yahoo.com','','165.98.223.21','2013-06-12 16:17:14','2013-06-12 16:17:14','This doesn\'t work for me, I follow the instructions to the \"t\" and I get a message saying it installed correctly and that is the last action it runs.I will continue my quest somewhere else for answers. I\'m running macbookpro8,1 with only Win8; mouse, k